Nasolabial folds begin to form at a young age, but become noticeable after 30-35 years.

 Their formation can be influenced not only by active facial expressions, but also by a decrease in skin tone, gravitational ptosis, and stress.

 The presence of nasolabial folds visually makes the face older than its age🙈

 Correction of the nasolabial triangle is performed with fillers, they even out the skin relief, replenishing volume, smoothing out wrinkles and folds.

 Sometimes, if a crease has already formed at the site of the fold, several procedures may be required for complete correction.

"NEW YOU"- Threads lifting: A new reverse 🔝 technique for correcting the lower third of the face by @Doctor.AMB. 
Points for implantation of threads are selected individually for each patient, in the place where the maximum stretching of tissues.
PDO therapy or Thread lifting is an effective cosmetic technique that lifts and tightens sagging skin tissues by inducing collagen production. It involves the implantation of fine, absorbable polydioxanone threads (similar to those used in medical suturing) into the subcutaneous layer of the skin using small needles.
Pail lavel: mild
💡Results: seen immediately or up to 2-5 weeks
🥼 Topically and local numbing is applied. 
🔊 lasts from 14 to 36 months depending on each individual.
Procedure time :30-50 min with a preparation time.

How long does it take for PDO threads to dissolve?

This will improve over a period of a couple of weeks as new collagen grows between the threads and gives further lift and tightening to the skin. 
The PDO threads gradually dissolve around 6 months, but the resulting lift remains.
